<p>In neighborhoods like Lawrenceville and the Strip District, where residential and commercial properties mix, solar installations can be particularly cost-effective due to higher energy consumption patterns. The North Hills suburbs, including areas like Ross Township and McCandless, typically feature newer homes with adequate roof space and southern exposure, making them ideal for larger solar installations. East End neighborhoods such as Point Breeze and Highland Park offer excellent opportunities for both solar and HVAC upgrades, with many homes featuring the optimal roof orientation and sufficient space for modern equipment installations.</p>

